# Premium Artistic Direction

## Scope

- **Existing brands** (`sweet-media`, `inner-peak-colorado`, `mental-health-for-teens`): Maintain their established Design DNA documented in the registry below. Do not introduce colors, fonts, motion patterns, or layout archetypes that conflict with a brand's registered choices.
- **New brands**: Before writing any component, complete the Design DNA Intake (8 axes below). Verify against the registry that your choices differ from every existing brand on at least 6 of 8 axes. Document choices in the registry before building.

## Design DNA Axes

Every brand must make one explicit choice per axis. No two brands may share the same choice on more than 2 of 8 axes.

### 1. Background Archetype
- `solid-dark-abstract` ‚Äî Solid dark color field with abstract SVG/geometric graphic element
- `photo-video-overlay` ‚Äî Full-bleed photography or video with gradient overlay
- `white-editorial` ‚Äî Clean white/light background, typography-first
- `texture-grain` ‚Äî Texture, noise, or organic grain as primary surface treatment
- `gradient-mesh-abstract` ‚Äî Gradient mesh or color-field abstraction as primary surface (no photography)
- `split-panel` ‚Äî Split-screen or asymmetric panel layout

### 2. Palette Temperature
- `cool-midnight` ‚Äî Deep navy/blue tones as primary
- `warm-forest` ‚Äî Forest green, sage, or muted earth as primary
- `neutral-sand` ‚Äî Sand, warm grey, or stone as primary
- `deep-plum` ‚Äî Purple, aubergine, or dark violet as primary
- `ocean-teal` ‚Äî Teal, seafoam, or aqua as primary
- `carbon-charcoal` ‚Äî Near-black charcoal or slate as primary

### 3. Hero Centerpiece
- `data-visualization` ‚Äî Animated or interactive data graphic (chart, orbit, dashboard)
- `editorial-photography` ‚Äî Art-directed photo or video with strong composition
- `full-typographic` ‚Äî Typography is the hero; no heavy imagery or graphic
- `product-showcase` ‚Äî Product, service, or UI demo as focal point
- `abstract-geometry` ‚Äî Abstract geometric or illustration-based centerpiece
- `split-content-panel` ‚Äî Equal-weight split between media and text/form

### 4. Typography Personality
- `editorial-serif-contrast` ‚Äî High weight-contrast serif (light italic + ultra-bold display)
- `editorial-serif-warmth` ‚Äî Moderate serif with organic tracking and small-caps accents
- `geometric-sans` ‚Äî Clean geometric sans-serif, precision-driven (e.g. Inter, DM Sans)
- `humanist-warmth` ‚Äî Rounded humanist sans, approachable and warm (e.g. Nunito, Lato)
- `display-contrast` ‚Äî Extreme size or weight contrast between display and body type
- `monospace-tech` ‚Äî Monospace or code-adjacent type treatment

### 5. Motion Language
- `ambient-particles-orbit` ‚Äî Particle canvas, orbit rings, or continuous background animation
- `static-cinematic` ‚Äî No hero animation; cinematic photography or stillness carries the moment
- `scroll-driven` ‚Äî Scroll-triggered reveals, parallax, or sticky transitions
- `micro-interactions-only` ‚Äî Motion confined to hover/focus/interaction states only
- `none` ‚Äî Intentionally motion-free throughout

### 6. Section Rhythm
- `dark-dominant` ‚Äî Dark background as primary; white used for contrast and breaks
- `alternating-cream` ‚Äî Light/neutral alternating cream or warm sections; dark only for emphasis
- `white-editorial` ‚Äî All-white or near-white surfaces; sections differentiated by type and spacing
- `editorial-magazine` ‚Äî Asymmetric editorial layout; mixed full-bleed and text-heavy sections
- `card-grid-driven` ‚Äî Grid of cards as the primary content structure
- `full-bleed-panels` ‚Äî Sequential full-viewport-height panels, each with a distinct treatment

### 7. Accent Treatment
- `warm-amber-copper` ‚Äî Amber, copper, or burnt orange accent
- `pure-white` ‚Äî No color accent; white on dark is the only contrast tool
- `electric-pop` ‚Äî A single saturated accent (coral, cyan, lime, electric blue, etc.)
- `muted-earth-tone` ‚Äî Terracotta, olive, or dusty rose accent
- `metallic-gold` ‚Äî Gold, champagne, or warm metallic accent
- `cool-mint` ‚Äî Mint, sage, or pale green accent

### 8. Brand Voice Signal
- `performance-ROI` ‚Äî Data, metrics, results-first; trust built through proof
- `care-sanctuary` ‚Äî Warmth, safety, and emotional resonance first
- `innovation-authority` ‚Äî Forward-thinking expertise; technology or category leadership
- `community-belonging` ‚Äî Identity-driven; community or cultural signal
- `clinical-trust` ‚Äî Medical credibility, credentials, and evidence-based language

