## Quality Standards

- Every site must feel premium, intentional, and visually elevated. Test: would a sophisticated client pay for this design?
- Use strong visual hierarchy, generous spacing, and restrained color use. Signal quality through what you leave out.
- Prefer fewer, high-impact visual elements over trend-heavy clutter or decorative excess.
- Every net-new page requires unique AI-generated images (see `platform-unique-page-imagery` rule).
- Icon system must be consistent per brand: same icon family, same stroke weight, same visual treatment site-wide.
- Keep aesthetics compatible with performance goals: optimized image sizing, selective decorative effects.
